<TITLE> Bullet-hit currency trader dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 04 (bdnews24.com)The bullet-hit currency trader of Gulshan died at the National Institute of Cardiovascular Diseases (NICVD) in the capital early on Thursday. Faruq Ahmed, 45, the owner of March Money Exchange at Gulshan 2, was shot by gunmen at around 10pm on Wednesday when he and his car driver Rana were going to Norda Joar Sahara from Gulshan by rickshaw. Rana said that the criminals had taken one of the two briefcases from them that had Tk 12 lakh. The criminals blocked their way with a private car in front of the Saudi Embassy and shot them when they started yelling. Both of them took bullets. The gunmen fled leaving the car behind when people chased them, said sub-inspector of Gulshan Police Station Giasuddin. Police recovered the car and a pistol from the spot, he added. They were first admitted to United Hospital and then to NICVD. bdne
